mosphere%20holds%20more%20moisture%2C%20which%20can%20result%20in%20heavy%20rains%20and%20flooding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20can%20damage%20schools%20or%20put%20them%20out%20of%20commission%20while%20they%20are%20used%20as%20shelters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHot%20weather%20can%20also%20drive%20wildfires%20and%20spikes%20in%20air%20pollution%2C%20which%20have%20caused%20school%20closures%20everywhere%20from%20India%20to%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20climate%20crisis%20is%20already%20a%20reality%20for%20children%20in%20East%20Asia%20and%20Pacific%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20UN%20children's%20agency%20UNICEF%20warned%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMohua%20Akter%20Nur%2C%2013%2C%20is%20living%20proof%20of%20that%20claim%2C%20sweltering%20in%20a%20one-room%20home%20in%20Bangladesh's%20capital%20Dhaka%20after%20her%20school%20closed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIntermittent%20electricity%20means%20she%20cannot%20even%20rely%20on%20a%20fan%20to%20cool%20the%20cramped%20dwelling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20heat%20is%20intolerable%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20AFP%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20school%20is%20shut%2C%20but%20I%20can't%20study%20at%20home.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPoorest%20hit%20hardest%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApril%20marked%20the%2011th%20straight%20month%20of%20record%20global%20heat%2C%20and%20the%20pattern%20is%20clear%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20said%20Shumon%20Sengupta%2C%20country%20director%20for%20NGO%20Save%20the%20Children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNot%20only%20are%20the%20temperatures%20higher%2C%20the%20duration%20of%20the%20high%20temperatures%20is%20much%20longer%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPreviously%2C%20few%20areas%20used%20to%20have%20these%20heatwaves%2C%20now%20the%20coverage%20of%20the%20country%20is%20much%20higher%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESchools%20across%20much%20of%20Asia%20are%20simply%20not%20equipped%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20growing%20consequences%20of%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBangladesh's%20urban%20schools%20can%20be%20sturdy%2C%20but%20are%20often%20overcrowded%2C%20with%20little%20ventilation%2C%20said%20Sengupta.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20rural%20areas%2C%20corrugated%20metal%20roofs%20can%20turn%20classrooms%20into%20ovens%2C%20and%20electricity%20for%20fans%20is%20unreliable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Bangladesh%20and%20elsewhere%2C%20students%20often%20walk%20long%20distances%20to%20and%20from%20school%2C%20risking%20heatstroke%20in%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20closing%20schools%20comes%20with%20serious%20consequences%2C%20%26quot%3Bparticularly%20for%20children%20from%20poorer%2C%20vulnerable%20communities%20who%20do%20not%20have%20access%20to%20resources%20such%20as%20computers%2C%20internet%20and%20books%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Salwa%20Aleryani%2C%20UNICEF's%20health%20specialist%20for%20East%20Asia%20and%20the%20Pacific.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20children%20%26quot%3Bare%20also%20less%20likely%20to%20have%20better%20conditions%20at%20home%20to%20protect%20them%20during%20heatwaves%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20may%20be%20left%20unsupervised%20by%20parents%20who%20cannot%20afford%20to%20stay%20home%2C%20and%20school%20closures%20put%20children%20at%20higher%20risk%20of%20child%20labour%2C%20child%20marriage%20and%20even%20trafficking%2C%20said%20Sengupta.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Wake%20up%20to%20this'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClimate%20change%20also%20threatens%20schooling%20indirectly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUNICEF%20research%20in%20Myanmar%20found%20that%20crop%20shortages%20caused%20by%20rising%20temperatures%20and%20unpredictable%20rain%20caused%20families%20to%20pull%20children%20from%20school%20to%20help%20with%20work%20or%20because%20they%20could%20no%20longer%20afford%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20wealthy%20countries%20in%20the%20region%20have%20taken%20steps%20to%20protect%20children's%20education%2