ipt%20of%20the%20conversation%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDavid%20Gura%3A%20Every%20year%2C%20the%20top%20executives%20at%20Apple%20-%20of%20course%2C%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20and%20most%20influential%20companies%20in%20the%20world%20-%20are%20whisked%20away%20to%20an%20idyllic%20retreat%20usually%20in%20Carmel%20Valley.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat's%20about%2090%20miles%20south%20of%20the%20company's%20headquarters%2C%20in%20Cupertino%2C%20California.%20So%2C%20many%20of%20these%20execs%20travel%20by%20bus.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMark%20Gurman%3A%20They%20can't%20bring%20their%20family%2C%20they%20can't%20bring%20their%20assistants.%20These%20are%20the%20100%20most%20important%20people%20at%20Apple.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20Bloomberg's%20Mark%20Gurman%20has%20covered%20Apple%20for%20almost%2015%20years%2C%20and%20he%20says%20this%20annual%20meeting%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20dates%20on%20the%20company's%20calendar.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20something%20Steve%20Jobs%20started.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGurman%3A%20They%20sit%20in%20auditoriums%2C%20different%20rooms%20of%20this%20beautiful%20resort%20in%20Northern%20California.%20They%20are%20taught%20and%20shown%20all%20of%20the%20goodness%20that's%20to%20come%20from%20Apple%20in%20the%20years%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20It%20was%20at%20this%20retreat%20that%20Apple's%20so-called%20%26quot%3BTop%20100%26quot%3B%20got%20a%20first%20look%20at%20the%20original%20iPad%2C%20Mark%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20saw%20the%20MacBook%20Air%20and%20the%20Apple%20Watch.%20And%20got%20updates%20on%20the%20Apple%20Car%20project%2C%20which%20the%20company%20just%20scrapped.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGurman%3A%20This%20is%20where%20you%20go%20to%20learn%20about%20Apple's%20future.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20And%20while%20most%20of%20the%20focus%20is%20on%20product%20presentations%20-%20and%20prototypes%2C%20Apple's%20senior%20leaders%20are%20also%20taking%20note%20of%20who%20among%20them%20has%20been%20picked%20to%20make%20these%20presentations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGurman%3A%20I%20think%20the%20people%20at%20that%20event%20are%20probably%20always%20naturally%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%20who's%20next%20in%20line.%20Who's%20in%20charge%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20That%20is%20...%20who%20will%20eventually%20replace%20Tim%20Cook.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJobs'%20hand-picked%20successor%20has%20been%20the%20CEO%20of%20Apple%20for%20nearly%20thirteen%20years.%20He%20was%20Jobs'%20deputy%20before%20that.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20At%20Apple%2C%20succession%20planning%20is%20the%20elephant%20in%20the%20room%2C%20and%20even%20though%20Cook%20hasn't%20indicated%20he%20plans%20to%20leave%20the%20company%20anytime%20soon%2C%20Mark%20says%20there%20is%20growing%20speculation%20about%20when%20that'll%20happen%20who%20will%20be%20its%20next%20chief%20executive%20-%20%C2%A0and%20whether%20that%20person%20is%20in%20this%20group%20of%20Apple's%20most%20important%20people.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGurman%3A%20We're%20nearing%20sort%20of%20the%20end%20of%20Cook's%20tenure%20at%20Apple%2C%20probably%2C%20right%3F%20He's%20going%20to%20turn%2065%20next%20year.%20He's%20older%20than%20most%20CEOs%20in%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500.%20He's%20been%20at%20Apple%20for%2025%20years%20and%20Apple's%20at%20a%20precarious%20position%20because%20the%20executive%20team%20where%20they%20likely%20would%20choose%20their%20next%20CEO%20from%20most%20of%20the%20people%20on%20that%20executive%20team%20are%20all%20about%2060%20years%20old%2C%20or%20would%20probably%20be%20in%20their%20mid%20to%20late%20sixties%20by%20the%20time%20Tim%20Cook%20retires%2C%20leaving%20the%20company%20with%20very%20few%20reasonable%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20Today%20on%20the%20show%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20challenges%20of%20finding%20someone%20who%20could%20do%20one%20of%20the%20most%20demanding%20jobs%20in%20business.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWho's%20in%20the%20running%2C%20and%20how%20that%20decision%20will%20impact%20a%20%242.8%20trillion%20company%2C%20and%20one%20of%20the%20best-known%20brands%20in%20the%20world.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI'm%20David%20Gura%2C%20and%20this%20is%20The%20Big%20Take%2C%20from%20Bloomberg%20News.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20Tim%20Cook%20has%20been%20the%20CEO%20of%20Apple%20for%20more%20than%20a%20decade.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20part%20of%20his%20job%20involves%20planning%20for%20who%20will%20succeed%20him.%20Bloomberg's%20Mark%20Gurman%20says%20it's%20not%20the%20easiest%20job%20to%20fill.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20Is%20that%20job%20description%20really%20well%20fleshed%20out%3F%20In%20other%20words%2C%20what%20does%20an%20Apple%20CEO%20need%20to%20be%20able%20to%20do%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGurman%3A%20An%20Apple%20CEO%20needs%20to%20either%20be%20the%20visionary%20to%20bring%20new%20products%20to%20market.%20Or%20needs%20to%20be%20able%20to%20find%20who%20the%20visionary%20is%20and%20partner%20with%20that%20visionary%20to%20bring%20those%20new%20products%20to%20market.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20It's%20a%20challenge%20that%20wasn't%20lost%20on%20Steve%20Jobs%20when%20he%20tapped%20Cook%20for%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGurman%3A%20You%20know%2C%20the%20thing%20about%20Cook%20is%20that%20it%20is%20all%20consuming%2C%20and%20I%20think%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20that%20Jobs%20made%20him%20the%20CEO%2C%20other%20than%20the%20fact%20that%20he%20was%20the%20most%20qualified%2C%20probably%20by%20a%20long%20shot%2C%20amongst%20the%20executive%20team%20at%20the%20time%2C%20is%20that%20Jobs%20knew%20how%20all%20consuming%20the%20next%20era%20of%20Apple%20would%20be%2C%20right%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20Tim's%20entire%20life%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20based%20on%20everyone%20who%20knows%20him%20and%20everyone%20you%20speak%20to%20about%20him%20is%20Apple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20Cook%20became%20Apple's%20CEO%20in%202011%2C%20under%20intense%20scrutiny.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20took%20over%20for%20Jobs%2C%20the%20company's%20founder%2C%20who%20was%20battling%20pancreatic%20cancer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20October%20of%20that%20year%2C%20Cook%20stepped%20into%20the%20spotlight%2C%20to%20unveil%20a%20new%20version%20of%20the%20iPhone%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETim%20Cook%3A%20Good%20morning.%20This%20is%20my%20first%20product%20launch%20since%20being%20named%20CEO.%20I'm%20sure%20you%20didn't%20know%20that.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20You%20can%20hear%20him%20cracking%20a%20joke%20to%20acknowledge%20what%20a%20big%20moment%20this%20was.%20He%20was%20under%20immense%20pressure%20-%20following%20in%20Jobs'%20footsteps.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECook%3A%20%C2%A0I%20Love%20Apple.%20And%20I%20consider%20it%20the%20privilege%20of%20a%20lifetime%20to%20have%20worked%20here%20for%20almost%2014%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20As%20Apple's%20chief%20operating%20officer%2C%20Cook%20worked%20side-by-side%20with%20Jobs%2C%20during%20a%20period%20when%20Apple%20grew%20at%20breakneck%20speed.%20When%20it%20became%20much%20more%20than%20a%20computer%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECook%3A%20Just%20ten%20years%20ago%2C%20we%20launched%20the%20original%20iPod%20here%2C%20and%20it%20went%20on%20to%20revolutionize%20the%20way%20we%20listen%20to%20music.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20Mark%2C%20you%20covered%20that%20transition%20in%202011.%20What%20can%20you%20tell%20us%20about%20the%20relationship%20between%20Steve%20Jobs%20and%20Tim%20Cook%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGurman%3A%20They%20were%20close.%20I%20wouldn't%20say%20that%20they%20were%20best%20friends.%20Uh%2C%20I%20would%20say%20in%20many%20ways%20they%20were%2C%20uh%2C%20partners.%20Steve%20Jobs%20was%20the%20design%20mind.%20He%20was%20the%20person%20dreaming%20up%20these%20new%20products%2C%20and%20Tim%20Cook%20was%20the%20execution%20guy.%20He%20was%20the%20person%20for%20all%20intents%20and%20purposes%2C%20who%20was%20able%20to%20bring%20these%20products%20to%20market%2C%20get%20them%20manufactured%2C%20get%20them%20into%20retail%20stores%2C%20and%20so%20forth.%20And%20then%20when%20Steve%20Jobs%20stepped%20down%20and%20then%20ultimately%20passed%20away%2C%20what%20Apple%20lost%20was%20sort%20of%20that%20visionary%20to%20dream%20up%20new%20types%20of%20product%20categories%2C%20new%20designs%2C%20new%20user%20experiences%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20Jobs%20died%20on%20October%205th%2C%202011%20-%20one%20day%20after%20Cook%20unveiled%20that%20new%20iPhone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20the%20years%20that%20followed%2C%20Cook%20made%20sure%20Apple%20continued%20to%20build%20on%20the%20runaway%20success%20of%20that%20device.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGurman%3A%20The%20Apple%20watch%20for%20all%20intents%20and%20purposes%20is%20an%20accessory%20or%20an%20extension%20of%20the%20iPhone.%20Airpods%20are%20an%20extension%20to%20the%20iPhone%2C%20an%20accessory%20to%20the%20iPhone.%20What%20Tim%20Cook%20has%20done%2C%20he's%20taken%20the%20product%20lines%20that%20Steve%20Jobs%20created%20and%20envisioned%2C%20and%20supercharged%20them.%20When%20Steve%20Jobs%20passed%2C%20there%20was%20only%20one%20iPad%20model%2C%20the%20iPad%202.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20there%20are%20five%2C%20or%20even%20more%20iPad%20models%20available%20right%20now.%20The%20iPhone%20went%20from%20one%20or%20two%20different%20models%20to%20several%20different%20models.%20So%20what%20Tim%20Cook%20has%20been%20able%20to%20do%20is%20squeeze%20so%20much%20juice%20out%20of%20the%20lemons%20that%20are%20those%20original%20Apple%20form%20factors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20Under%20his%20leadership%2C%20Apple%20added%20products%20and%20services%2C%20along%20with%20new%20accessories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20branched%20into%20movies%20and%20TV.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20introduced%20an%20Apple%20credit%20card.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGurman%3A%20At%20its%20core%2C%20I%20think%20Apple%20is%20still%20very%20much%20a%20technology%20company%2C%20but%20they%20like%20to%20position%20themselves%20as%20well%20as%20a%20lifestyle%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20Now%2C%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20into%20his%20tenure%2C%20do%20you%20see%20this%20company%20as%20Tim%20Cook's%20Apple%2C%20or%20is%20it%20still%20Steve%20Jobs'%20Apple%20that%2C%20that%20Tim%20Cook%20is%20the%20steward%20of%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGurman%3A%20I%20think%20it's%20actually%20a%20mix%20of%20both.%20At%20its%20very%20core%2C%20Steve%20Jobs%20left%20Apple%20with%20something%2C%20you%20know%2C%20more%20than%20pretty%20good%20in%20the%20iPhone.%20And%20Tim%20Cook%2C%20I%20would%20say%2C%20has%20probably%20made%20the%20most%20of%20what%20he%20was%20left%20with.%20I%20don't%20think%20anyone%20could%20have%20done%20a%20better%20job%20following%20in%20the%20footsteps%20as%20legendary%20as%20someone%20like%20Steve%20Jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20People%20worried%20Steve%20Jobs%20would%20be%20irreplaceable%2C%20but%20now%2C%20there's%20a%20sense%20Tim%20Cook's%20shoes%20will%20be%20hard%20to%20fill.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGurman%3A%20So%20The%20question%20is%20Apple%20moving%20forward%2C%20who%20was%20that%20new%20person%20to%20lead%20Apple%20into%20a%20new%20era%20with%20a%20new%20vision%2C%20with%20new%20types%20of%20products.%20And%20that's%20really%20what%20Apple%20needs%20to%20come%20up%20with%20to%20create%20its%20next%2015%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20There%20are%20a%20handful%20of%20names%20that%20come%20up%20in%20conversations%20about%20CEO%20succession%20at%20Apple.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20over%20the%20years%2C%20as%20Mark%20has%20reported%20on%20this%2C%20there's%20been%20a%20clear%20frontrunner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGurman%3A%20He%20can%20own%20the%20stage.%20He%20can%20talk%20the%20talk%20with%20government%20officials%20from%20China%20to%20Europe%20to%20the%20US.%20If%20something%20happened%20unexpectedly%20to%20Cook%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20Apple%20would%20miss%20a%20beat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20So%2C%20who%20is%20Apple's%20heir%20apparent%3F%20And%20who%20else%20is%20waiting%20in%20the%20wings%2C%20vying%20for%20the%20top%20job%3F%20That's%20after%20the%20break.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20Before%20Tim%20Cook%20became%20Apple's%20CEO%2C%20he%20was%20the%20chief%20operating%20officer%20under%20Steve%20Jobs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20who%20will%20replace%20Cook%2C%20his%20current%20COO%20could%20easily%20be%20next%20in%20line%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECook%3A%20And%20to%20tell%20us%20about%20some%20progress%20in%20this%20area%2C%20I'd%20like%20to%20invite%20up%20Jeff%20Williams.%20Jeff%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20That's%20Cook%20introducing%20Jeff%20Williams%20at%20a%20product%20launch%20in%202016%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWilliams%3A%20Last%20year%2C%20we%20introduced%20Research%20Kit.%20And%20our%20goal%20was%20to%20use%20technology%20to%20solve%20some%20of%20the%20biggest%20problems%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20Williams%20has%20been%20C-O-O%20for%20almost%20a%20decade%20now.%20He%20joined%20the%20company%20in%201998.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGurman%3A%20Right%20now%2C%20he%20runs%20Apple's%20entire%20operations.%20He's%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20Apple%20supply%20chain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe's%20in%20charge%20of%20Apple's%20health%20care%20efforts.%20He's%20in%20charge%20of%20Apple%20watch%20hardware%20and%20software%20engineering.%20He%20was%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20Apple%20car.%20He's%20involved%20with%20the%20Apple%20vision%20pro%20headset%2C%20and%20he's%20in%20charge%20of%20Apple's%20hardware%20and%20software%20design%20organization.%20So%20he%20has%20so%20much%20in%20his%20portfolio%20already%2C%20and%20he%20would%20be%20able%20to%20be%20a%20shoo-in%20pretty%20easily%20for%20Cook%20if%20something%20were%20to%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20people%20have%20called%20him%20Tim%20Cook's%20Tim%20Cook.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20And%20like%20Cook%2C%20Williams%20grew%20up%20in%20the%20South%2C%20he%20got%20an%20MBA%20from%20Duke%2C%20and%20had%20a%20stint%20at%20IBM%20before%20joining%20Apple.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20there's%20something%20else%20these%20two%20have%20in%20common.%20They're%20both%20in%20their%20early%20sixties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGurman%3A%20He's%20only%20two%20years%20younger%20than%20Cook.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20And%20that%20could%20make%20William's%20path%20to%20succeeding%20Cook%20complicated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGurman%3A%20If%20Cook%20retires%20in%20three%20to%20five%20years%2C%20you%20can't%20name%20a%2066%20year%20old%20Jeff%20Williams%20as%20CEO%20of%20Apple.%20Right%3F%20The%20Street%2C%20the%20market%2C%20the%20employees%2C%20the%20board%2C%20probably%20wouldn't%20be%20terribly%20fond%20of%20that%20idea.%20You%20can't%20set%20up%20someone%20for%20a%20two%20to%20five%20year%20tenure%20as%20a%20new%20CEO%20of%20a%20company%20as%20big%20and%20as%20important%20as%20Apple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20This%20is%20not%20just%20an%20issue%20with%20Williams%2C%20though.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20go%20down%20the%20list%20of%20other%20potential%20candidates%20among%20Apple's%20top%20management%2C%20a%20trend%20emerges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMark%20says%20many%20members%20of%20the%20company's%20leadership%20team%20are%20also%20hovering%20around%20retirement%20age.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20turnover%20at%20the%20executive%20level%20is%20pretty%20rare.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGurman%3A%20When%20you're%20a%20Senior%20Vice%20President%20at%20Apple%2C%20you're%20essentially%20the%20CEO%20of%20a%20major%20division%2C%20right%3F%20You're%20at%20one%20of%20the%20most%20successful%20companies%20in%20the%20world.%20You're%20also%20getting%20paid%20%2425%20million%20per%20year%20as%20an%20Apple%20Senior%20Vice%20President.%20So%20from%20a%20financial%20standpoint%2C%20it's%20very%20worthwhile%20to%20stay%20around.%20But%20I%20think%20the%20people%20in%20Apple's%20executive%20team%2C%20they're%20motivated%20by%20more%20than%20money.%20I%20think%20there's%20a%20sense%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20these%20folks%20are%20very%20much%20motivated%20by%20the%20power%20that%20comes%20with%20being%20in%20that%20role.%20And%20so%20power%20is%20sometimes%20hard%20to%20give%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20Mark%20says%2C%20if%20it's%20not%20Williams%2C%20there%20are%20a%20few%20other%20candidates%20who%20are%20likely%20in%20the%20running.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey're%20all%20currently%20on%20the%20Apple%20payroll.%20Tim%20Cook%20himself%20has%20said%20he%20hopes%20the%20board%20taps%20someone%20from%20within%20the%20company.%20And%20they%20have%20their%20own%20trade-offs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinding%20a%20single%20person%20who%20can%20do%20everything%20that%20an%20Apple%20CEO%20needs%20to%20do%20is%20a%20real%20challenge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20potential%20candidate%20is%20on%20his%20second%20stint%20at%20Apple%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGurman%3A%20Craig%20Federighi%2C%20who's%20in%20charge%20of%20software%20engineering.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20But%2C%20Mark%20says%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGurman%3A%20Federighi%20probably%20doesn't%20have%20the%20business%20acumen%20to%20run%20the%20whole%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20There's%20also%20Deirdre%20O'Brien%2C%20who%20oversees%20Apple's%20sprawling%20retail%20operation%20worldwide.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGurman%3A%20And%20before%20that%2C%20Uh%2C%20she%20was%20one%20of%20the%20company's%20top%20executives%20on%20operations%20and%20sales.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20But%20according%20to%20Mark%3F%20...%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGurman%3A%20Apple%20probably%20wants%20to%20try%20something%20new%20for%20a%20new%20era%20and%20not%20go%20with%20another%20operations%20or%20an%20HR%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20But%20Mark%20has%20identified%20another%20candidate.%20Who%2C%20with%20his%20age%20and%20experience%2C%20is%20a%20strong%20contender.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGurman%3A%20Everything%20that%20I%20have%20learned%20while%20reporting%20the%20story%20points%20to%20a%20guy%20named%20John%20Ternus.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20is%20not%20even%2050%20years%20old.%20He's%20Apple's%20senior%20vice%20president%20of%20Hardware%20Engineering.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20joined%20Apple's%20executive%20team%20in%202021.%20He%20has%20quickly%20risen%20through%20the%20ranks.%20He%20used%20to%20be%20a%20VP%20in%20charge%20of%20Mac%20computer%20engineering.%20He%20eventually%20added%20the%20iPad%2C%20added%20AirPods.%20More%20recently%2C%20he%20added%20the%20iPhone%20and%20the%20Apple%20watch.%20And%20now%20he's%20in%20charge%20of%20basically%20all%20of%20the%20money%20making%20hardware%20for%20Apple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20he's%20become%20an%20increasingly%20important%20face%20at%20the%20company.%20He's%20been%20increasingly%20promoted%20in%20their%20marketing.%20He's%20dealing%20with%20regulators%20in%20terms%20of%20right%20to%20repair%20laws.%20So%20he's%20becoming%20a%20bigger%20part%20of%20the%20Apple%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20Mark%20says%20Ternus%20had%20a%20marquee%20role%20this%20year%2C%20at%20that%20annual%20executive%20conference%20in%20Northern%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20just%20this%20week%2C%20Apple%20unveiled%20some%20new%20tech%2C%20and%20Cook%20called%20on%20Ternus%20at%20that%20event%20to%20introduce%20those%20new%20products%20to%20the%20public.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETim%20Cook%3A%20So%20here's%20John%20to%20tell%20you%20more.%20...%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJohn%20Ternus%3A%20Let's%20kick%20things%20off%20with%20iPad%20Air.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20Mark%20says%20Ternus'%20prospects%20of%20becoming%20Apple's%20next%20CEO%20get%20better%20the%20longer%20Cook%20sticks%20around.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20there%20is%20no%20indication%20he%20plans%20to%20retire%20anytime%20soon.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExecutives%20are%20not%20under%20the%20same%20pressure%20they%20used%20to%20be%2C%20to%20retire%20in%20their%20mid-Sixties.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20Mark%2C%20I%20wonder%20if%20you%20could%20situate%20this%20conversation%20in%20kind%20of%20a%20broader%20cultural%20sea%20change%20we're%20seeing.%20Bob%20Iger%20back%20at%20Disney%20in%20his%2070s.%20That%20must%20in%20some%20way%20sort%20of%20liberate%20Tim%20Cook%20to%20look%20perhaps%20at%20a%20longer%20tenure%20at%20Apple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGurman%3A%20Yeah%2C%20that's%20a%20very%20good%20point.%20Certainly%20the%20next%20U.%20S.%20president%20is%20going%20to%20be%20in%20their%2080s%20during%20their%20tenure.%20You%20have%20Pat%20Gelsinger%2C%20who's%20the%20CEO%20of%20Intel.%20He%20was%20named%20to%20that%20role%20three%20years%20ago%20when%20he%20was%20about%2060.%20So%20certainly%20you%20do%20have%20some%20older%20statesmen%20there%20with%20Tim%20Cook%2C%20you%20know%2C%20one%20of%20the%2C%20the%2C%20the%20older%20ones%20and%20Apple%20appreciates%2C%20as%20some%20people%20tell%20me%2C%20the%20people%20with%20gray%20hair%20there%2C%20that%20means%20they%20have%20experience%20and%20wisdom%2C%20and%20they've%20been%20around%20the%20block%20a%20few%20times.%20There%20is%20nothing%20that%20Tim%20Cook%20hasn't%20seen%2C%20and%20wisdom%20goes%20a%20long%20way%20for%20being%20an%20Apple%20executive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20For%20his%20part%2C%20Cook%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20unfinished%20business%20he's%20attending%20to%20right%20now%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApple's%20seen%20a%20slowdown%20in%20sales%2C%20the%20company%20is%20taking%20hits%20from%20regulators%20-%20in%20the%20US%20and%20the%20European%20Union%2C%20and%20after%20Apple's%20adventure%20in%20automobile%20manufacturing%20came%20to%20a%20screeching%20halt%2C%20it's%20under%20pressure%20to%20deliver%20something%20new.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20that%2C%20and%20more%2C%20is%20on%20Cook's%20plate%2C%20and%20Mark%20says%20no%20one%20is%20pushing%20him%20to%20step%20aside.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGurman%3A%20There's%20no%20mandatory%20retirement%20age.%20And%20I%20would%20say%20that%20even%20if%20there%20was%2C%20uh%2C%20they'd%20rip%20that%20up%20or%20shred%20it%20or%20light%20it%20on%20fire%20to%20let%20Cook%20stay%20around%20as%20long%20as%20he%20wants%20to.%20Because%20he's%20been%20effective%2C%20Wall%20Street%20loves%20him.%20The%20stock%20price%20has%20surely%20been%20positively%20reflected%20by%20Cook's%20tenure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20so%20I%20think%20Tim%20Cook%20is%20going%20to%20be%20the%20CEO%20of%20Apple%20as%20long%20as%20he%20wants%20to%20be%20the%20CEO%20of%20Apple%20and%20he%20won't%20step%20down%20a%20day%20before%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGura%3A%20This%20is%20The%20Big%20Take%2C%20from%20Bloomberg%20News.%20I'm%20David%20Gura.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715229780000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-04%2Fikmnao7_tim-cook_625x300_17_April_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fmeet-tim-cooks-tim-cook-who-could-be-apples-next-ceo-5622281%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Tim%20Cook%20picked%20up%20the%20mantle%20from%20Steve%20Jobs%20as%20CEO%20of%20Apple%20over%20a%20decade%20ago%20and%20grew%20it%20into%20a%20multi-trillion%20dollar%20company.%20Now%2C%20as%20Cook%20nears%20traditional%20retirement%20age%2C%20speculation%20abounds%20about%20who%20will%20succeed%20him.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fmeet-tim-cooks-tim-cook-who-could-be-apples-next-ceo-5622281%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fmeet-tim-cooks-tim-cook-who-could-be-apples-next-ceo-5622281%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fmeet-tim-cooks-tim-cook-who-could-be-apple