%20unbearable%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Vinaya%20K%2C%20a%20Bengaluru%20resident%2C%20highlighting%20how%20the%20incessant%20heat%20has%20disrupted%20her%20daily%20life.%20Despite%20experiencing%20a%20day%20of%20relief%20with%20some%20rain%2C%20the%20city%20is%20still%20facing%20a%20dry%20spell%20of%20over%20150%20days%2C%20and%20the%20heat%20continues%20to%20prevail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20Meteorological%20Department%20describes%20heat%20waves%20as%20occurring%20when%20the%20maximum%20temperature%20in%20plains%20reaches%20at%20least%2040%20degrees%20Celsius%20or%20more%2C%20and%20at%20least%2030%20degrees%20Celsius%20or%20more%20in%20hilly%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20department%20has%20issued%20a%20warning%20for%20hotter%20temperatures%20across%20several%20states%20in%20the%20coming%20weeks.%20According%20to%20a%20report%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Times%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20temperatures%20have%20soared%20between%2040%20to%2045%20degrees%20Celsius%20in%20parts%20of%20Odisha%20earlier%20this%20week.%20Similar%20conditions%20have%20been%20observed%20in%20Gangetic%20West%20Bengal%2C%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20Vidarbha%2C%20and%20southwestern%20parts%20of%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20among%20other%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERising%20temperatures%20lead%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20use%20of%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F281434%2Fagra-data-scientist-builds-solar-power-eco-friendly-air-conditioner-exalta%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20air%20conditioners%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20electricity%20as%20people%20try%20to%20escape%20the%20heat.%20%E2%80%9CWorking%20from%20home%20becomes%20more%20challenging%20as%20the%20temperature%20starts%20to%20rise%20as%20early%20as%207%20am.%20Living%20in%20apartments%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20allow%20us%20much%20room%20to%20naturally%20cool%20the%20space%2C%E2%80%9D%20Vinaya%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20situation%20may%20seem%20bleak%2C%20architects%20and%20designers%20suggest%2C%20depending%20on%20your%20geography%2C%20a%20few%20steps%20to%20keep%20your%20home%20naturally%20cool.%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20spoke%20with%20several%20experts%20to%20learn%20about%20the%20secrets%20of%20designing%20a%20%E2%80%98cool%E2%80%99%20house.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EGoing%20Back%20To%20Your%20Roots%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20look%20back%20at%20the%20houses%20that%20our%20ancestors%20built%2C%20the%20structures%20with%20open%20spaces%2C%20inward-looking%20homes%20with%20courtyards%20and%20huge%20windows%20helped%20to%20keep%20the%20home%20naturally%20cool.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESamira%20Rathod%2C%20an%20architect%20and%20designer%2C%20applied%20similar%20techniques%20to%20make%20a%20%E2%80%9CCool%20House%E2%80%9D%20located%20in%20Gujarat.%20The%20architect%20decided%20to%20utilise%20the%20wind%2C%20design%20and%20cooling%20materials%20to%20build%20and%20cool%20down%20the%20house.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20architect%20suggests%20using%20the%20wind%20in%20a%20way%20that%20it%20travels%20through%20the%20home%20making%20it%20cooler.%20For%20the%20cool%20house%20located%20in%20Gujarat%2C%20she%20used%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctrack-like%20design%20with%20rooms%20on%20either%20side%20of%20the%20house%20with%20a%20courtyard%20to%20help%20the%20wind%20circulate.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201067px)%20100vw%2C%201067px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F71e1f2ce8e654135b509da9fba6c6619_311592766_142412935197808_3738696823372802622_n-1680175563.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221067%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Going%20back%20to%20traditional%20designs%20and%20making%20use%20of%20natural%20materials%20to%20build%20a%20naturally%20cool%20house.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.c